[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aaron Schock: Ex Illinois congressman charged over spending scandal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An Illinois congressman who resigned amid a spending scandal including the remodelling of his office on the TV series Downton Abbey has been charged over questionable use of funds.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Aaron Schock will face 24 counts for alleged offences including wire fraud and filing false tax returns.
Mr Schock had been investigated for his real estate deals, and for spending taxpayer cash on private jets.
His lawyer said the 52-page indictment was nothing but "made-up allegations".
